<eesti> Seoses sellega tuleb r&otilde;hutada, et mitmed alternatiivv&otilde;rke kasutavad liberaliseeritud teenuste operaatorid rendivad piisava varul&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime tagamiseks igal juhul liine lisaks ka OTE-lt. </eesti>
<inglise> Given the expected growth in the leased-lines market, OTE could probably maintain its total profits in this area even if it introduces volume discounts on its current leased lines tariffs, to further align them with the underlying costs. </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;ttes arvesse eeldatavat p&uuml;siliinituru kasvu, v&otilde;iks OTE t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt s&auml;ilitada oma kogukasumi k&otilde;nealuses valdkonnas ka siis, kui ta kehtestab oma praegustele p&uuml;siliiniteenuse tariifidele mahup&otilde;hised allahindlused, et viia need tariifid veelgi rohkem vastavusse neile tehtud kulutustega. </eesti>
<inglise> Development of trade </inglise>
<eesti> Kaubanduse areng </eesti>
<inglise> (51) As a consequence of its monopoly for the provision of public telecommunications infrastructures, OTE is the sole supplier of leased lines and interconnection to providers of liberalized services. </inglise>
<eesti> 51) &Uuml;ldkasutatavate telekommunikatsiooniinfrastruktuuride pakkumise monopoli t&otilde;ttu on OTE ainus, kes pakub liberaliseeritud teenuste osutajatele p&uuml;siliiniteenust ja sidumisteenust. </eesti>
<inglise> It therefore determines to a large extent the costs of its competitors in the liberalized services sector. </inglise>
<eesti> Seega m&auml;&auml;rab OTE suurel m&auml;&auml;ral oma konkurentide kulusid liberaliseeritud teenuste valdkonnas. </eesti>
<inglise> This is shown inter alia by the abovementioned current high tariffs for leased lines, which make the supply of some liberalized services uneconomic. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda n&auml;itavad muu hulgas ka eespool nimetatud praegused k&otilde;rged p&uuml;siliiniteenuse tariifid, mille t&otilde;ttu ei ole m&otilde;nede liberaliseeritud teenuste osutamine majanduslikult tasuv. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, this potential knowledge by OTE of the costs of its competitors will increasingly affect trade, since OTE is likely to develop even further the liberalized services it offers, although this growth is likely to be slow in the short term. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti m&otilde;jutavad OTE v&otilde;imalikud teadmised oma konkurentide kulude kohta &uuml;ha enam kaubandust, sest t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt arendab OTE enda pakutavaid liberaliseeritud teenuseid veelgi edasi, kuigi usutavasti j&auml;&auml;b k&otilde;nealune kasv l&auml;hiajal aeglaseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas OTE could use its own infrastructure to provide such services, competitors providing global liberalized services, such as VPN or voice services to closed user groups, would thus be obliged to rely only on circuits leased from the operator they want to compete with. </inglise>
<eesti> OTE v&otilde;ib selliste teenuste osutamiseks kasutada oma infrastruktuure, kuid konkurendid, kes osutavad liberaliseeritud teenuseid, n&auml;iteks virtuaalse erav&otilde;rgu teenust v&otilde;i k&otilde;neteenust kinnistele kasutajar&uuml;hmadele, peaksid sellisel juhul s&otilde;ltuma selliselt operaatorilt renditud liinidest, kellega nad tahavad konkureerida. </eesti>
<inglise> This situation would be aggravated by the fact that OTE currently does not produce accounts which are sufficiently transparent to allow an adequate separation of its activities in the monopoly sector from those in the liberalized sector. </inglise>
<eesti> Olukorra keerulisust s&uuml;vendaks veelgi asjaolu, et OTE-l ei ole praegu piisavalt l&auml;bipaistvat raamatupidamiss&uuml;steemi, mis v&otilde;imaldaks n&otilde;uetekohaselt eraldada nende tegevuse monopoolses sektoris ja liberaliseeritud sektoris. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, there is no structural separation, to prevent staff in the infrastructure side of OTE from passing information to colleagues selling liberalized services. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti puudub struktuuriline eraldatus, mis aitaks v&auml;ltida seda, et OTE infrastruktuuride valdkonnas t&ouml;&ouml;tavad inimesed edastavad teavet liberaliseeritud teenuste m&uuml;&uuml;giga tegelevatele kolleegidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Conclusion </inglise>
<eesti> J&auml;reldus </eesti>
<inglise> (52) There are less restrictive regulatory means to prevent the bypassing of the voice-telephony monopoly until 1 January 2000 and such means could be implemented by EET which was set up in Greece, but which is not yet fully operational. </inglise>
<eesti> 52) Selleks et takistada k&otilde;nesidemonopolist m&ouml;&ouml;dahiilimist kuni 1. jaanuarini 2000, on olemas ka v&auml;hem piiravaid reguleerivaid meetmeid, ja selliseid meetmeid v&otilde;ib rakendada EET, mis on Kreekas juba loodud, kuid mis pole veel t&auml;ielikult valmis tegevust alustama. </eesti>
<inglise> Given that the presidential decree defining the staff regulations of EET will be in force by 1 August 1997, allowing EET to be fully operational by 1 October 1997, the granting of an additional implementation period extending after that date does not therefore seem justified. </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;ttes arvesse, et presidendi dekreet, milles s&auml;testatakse EET personalieeskirjad, j&otilde;ustub enne 1. augustit 1997 ja sellega muutub EET t&auml;ielikult t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imeliseks 1. oktoobriks 1997, ei ole kauem kui nimetatud kuup&auml;evani kestev lisarakendusaeg &otilde;igustatud. </eesti>
<inglise> (53) The Commission therefore considers that the development of trade resulting from the granting to Greece of an additional implementation period regarding the liberalization of alternative infrastructures is not affected to such an extent as to be contrary to the interests of the Community provided that the abovementioned period does not extend beyond 1 October 1997, </inglise>
<eesti> 53) Seep&auml;rast leiab komisjon, et kui Kreekale antakse alternatiivse infrastruktuuri liberaliseerimiseks lisaaega, ei m&otilde;juta see kaubanduse arengut sellisel m&auml;&auml;ral, et see oleks vastuolus &uuml;henduse huvidega, kui eespool nimetatud lisaaeg ei kesta kauem kui 1. oktoobrini 1997, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Greece may postpone until 31 December 2000 the abolition of the exclusive rights currently granted to the Hellenic Telecommunications Organization AE as regards the provision of voice telephony and the establishment and provision of public telecommunications networks, provided that the following conditions are implemented according to the following timetable: </inglise>
<eesti> Kreeka v&otilde;ib 31. detsembrini 2000 edasi l&uuml;kata Hellenic Telecommunications Organization AE praeguste k&otilde;nesideteenuse osutamist ja &uuml;ldkasutatavate telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rkude loomist ja pakkumist k&auml;sitlevate ainu&otilde;iguste kaotamise, kui j&auml;rgmisi tingimusi t&auml;idetakse esitatud ajakava kohaselt: </eesti>
<inglise> - no later than 1 October 1997, instead of 1 July 1996: notification to the Commission of all measures necessary to lift restrictions on the provision of already liberalized telecommunications services on: </inglise>
<eesti> - hiljemalt 1. oktoobriks 1997, mitte 1. juuliks 1996: teatatakse komisjonile k&otilde;igist meetmetest, mis on vajalikud selleks, et kaotada piirangud juba liberaliseeritud telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutamiseks, kasutades: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) networks established by the provider of the telecommunications service; </inglise>
<eesti> a) telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutaja loodud v&otilde;rke; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) infrastructures provided by third parties; </inglise>
<eesti> b) kolmandate isikute pakutavaid infrastruktuure; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the sharing of networks, other facilities and sites, </inglise>
<eesti> c) v&otilde;rkude, muude rajatiste ja vahendite jagamist; </eesti>
<inglise> - no later than nine months after the adoption of this Decision, instead of 11 January 1997: notification to the Commission of legislative changes necessary to implement full competition by 31 December 2000, including proposals for the funding of universal services, </inglise>
<eesti> - hiljemalt &uuml;heksa kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmist, mitte 11. jaanuariks 1997: teatatakse komisjonile &otilde;igusaktide muutmistest, mis on vajalikud, et 31. detsembriks 2000 ellu viia t&auml;ielik konkurents, sealhulgas ettepanekud universaalteenuste rahastamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> - no later than 31 December 1999, instead of 1 January 1997: notification to the Commission of draft licences for voice telephony and/or underlying network-providers, </inglise>
<eesti> - hiljemalt 31. detsembriks 1999, mitte 1. jaanuariks 1997: teatatakse komisjonile k&otilde;neteenuste osutajate ja/v&otilde;i selleks vajaliku v&otilde;rgu pakkujate kavandatavatest litsentsidest; </eesti>
<inglise> - no later than 30 June 2000, instead of 1 July 1997: publication of licensing conditions for public voice telephony and of interconnection charges as appropriate in accordance in both cases with relevant Community directives, </inglise>
<eesti> - hiljemalt 30. juuniks 2000, mitte 1. juuliks 1997: avaldatakse &uuml;ldkasutatava k&otilde;neside litsentsimistingimused ja sidumistasud vastavalt kummalgi puhul kehtivatele &uuml;henduse direktiividele; </eesti>
<inglise> - no later than 31 December 2000, instead of 1 January 1998: award of licences and amendment of existing licenses to enable competitive provision of voice telephony. </inglise>
<eesti> - hiljemalt 31. detsembriks 2000, mitte 1. jaanuariks 1998: antakse litsentsid ja muudetakse kehtivaid litsentse, et v&otilde;imaldada k&otilde;nesideteenuse osutamist konkurentsitingimuste kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Greece may postpone until 1 October 1997 the lifting of restrictions on the provision of already liberalized telecommunications services on: </inglise>
<eesti> Kreeka v&otilde;ib 1. oktoobrini 1997 edasi l&uuml;kata nende piirangute kaotamise, mis k&auml;sitlevad juba liberaliseeritud telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutamist, kasutades: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) networks established by the provider of the telecommunications service; </inglise>
<eesti> a) telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutaja loodud v&otilde;rke; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) infrastructures provided by third parties; </inglise>
<eesti> b) kolmandate isikute pakutavaid infrastruktuure; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) shared networks, other facilities and sites. </inglise>
<eesti> c) jagatud v&otilde;rke, muid rajatisi ja vahendeid. </eesti>
<inglise> Greece shall notify to the Commission, no later than 1 October 1997 instead of 1 July 1996, all measures adopted to lift such restrictions. </inglise>
<eesti> Kreeka teatab komisjonile k&otilde;igist selliste piirangute kaotamiseks v&otilde;etud meetmetest hiljemalt 1. oktoobriks 1997, mitte 1. juuliks 1996. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Hellenic Republic. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud Kreeka Vabariigile. </eesti>
